---

<head>
  <title>{t('getinvolved.title')} — BoycottWithAI</title>
  <meta name="description" content={t('getinvolved.subtitle')} />
</head>

<Base>
  <section>
    <h1>{t('getinvolved.title')}</h1>
    <p class="muted">{t('getinvolved.subtitle')}</p>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>Current Situation: 2024–2025</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Humanitarian crisis:</strong> Over 30,000 civilians killed in Gaza (OCHA, 2024), mass displacement in Sudan and Yemen, and record attacks on civilian infrastructure. UN agencies warn of famine and blocked aid.</li>
        <li><strong>Climate breakdown:</strong> 2024 saw record CO₂ emissions and over 40 million climate refugees (IDMC). COP28 failed to deliver binding fossil fuel phase-out.</li>
        <li><strong>Institutional failure:</strong> UN Security Council blocked by vetoes; EU and G7 increase arms exports and military budgets, ignoring calls for ceasefire and humanitarian access.</li>
        <li><strong>What you can do now:</strong> Start a micro-campaign: pick a local target (e.g. arms contract, fossil fuel project), use the petition/email templates, and log every reply. Share your results with local media and advocacy groups. Even 10 signatures or one MP reply can trigger press coverage or council debate.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="muted">Data sources: OCHA, SIPRI, IDMC, UNHCR, ACLED. See <a href="/en/resources/">resources</a> for templates and guides.</p>
